{"id":"ko2-tools-662","title":"ARCH-010: Move SampleFormat to src/core/ to fix TUI→CLI layer violation","description":"SampleFormat (src/cli/display.py:29-77) is a domain-level formatting utility imported by both CLI and TUI layers. src/tui/app.py:24 and src/tui/ui.py:15 import it from cli.display, creating a TUI→CLI dependency that violates the three-layer architecture (Core←CLI, Core←TUI). Combined with ko2-tools-6a8 (CLI→TUI via WaveformStore), this forms a bidirectional circular dependency between the two presentation layers.

Fix: Move SampleFormat to src/core/formatting.py (or src/core/display.py). Update imports in cli/display.py, tui/app.py, tui/ui.py. This is the highest-impact architectural fix — it and ko2-tools-6a8 together break the circular dependency.

Evidence: src/tui/app.py:24, src/tui/ui.py:15 both have 'from cli.display import SampleFormat'.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"ivan123.public@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-03-21T19:00:46Z","created_by":"Ivan Cherniukh","updated_at":"2026-03-21T19:00:46Z"}
